Hi, Lilei.

It&#39;s not completely clear what you&#39;re referring to without additional 
context, so it&#39;s hard to give a definitive answer. Are you referring to 
the &quot;isPageKnown&quot; test from the Chakrabarti book? If so, then the answer 
is &quot;no&quot; -- Heritrix does not check a page&#39;s content-hash against an 
index of all previously-seen pages before performing link-extraction or 
page-storage.

(heritrix maintains an &#39;URL seen&#39; structure, handled by implementing 
classes of the UriUniqFilter interface, and has several options for 
reducing the storage of duplicate copies of the same content at the same 
URL at a later time, but doesn&#39;t maintain a live index of all 
page-content seen. The benefits of such an index are too small for the 
overhead, in our typical uses.)

- Gordon @ IA

